subSubSection.paragraph:
Ultimate legs straight and relatively slender, the left leg is longer than the right (to be interpreted as a developmental defect or regeneration) (
Table 1
); prefemur and femur glabrous, tibia and tarsi with dense bristles (
Figs 8–11
, 
14–15
); ventral spinous process of the prefemur long, dorsomedial spinous process short (
Fig. 17
).
